# We welcome contributions from the academic and research community to improve MedMaintBot, our AI-powered chatbot prototype for medical device maintenance.


## 📝 Sign-off on Commits (DCO)

This repository requires all contributors to **sign off on their commits** to certify that they have the right to submit the code and that it complies with the project’s license.

The sign-off is a simple line at the end of your commit message, which looks like this:

    Signed-off-by: Your Name <your.email@example.com>

You can add this automatically by using the `-s` flag when committing:

```bash
git commit -s -m "Fix device parsing bug"

# How you can contribute
Report bugs → Open a GitHub Issue or use our bug report form
Suggest features or improvements → Share your ideas via this suggestion form
Improve documentation → Fix typos, clarify instructions, or extend usage guides.
🛠 Submit code contributions → Fork the repo, implement your changes, and open a Pull Request (PR).

Researchers who wish to obtain the documents and synthetic results used for testing MedMaintBot can request access through the following form:

👉 [Prototype Testing Request Form](https://forms.gle/jLByMYBmoQLZhnnR9)
